<TITLE> APJ Abdul Kalam arrives in Dhaka </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 18 (bdnews24.com)  Former Indian president APJ Abdul Kalam arrived in Bangladesh on Sunday for a three-day visit. Kalam, who landed in Dhaka on a Jet Airways flight from Delhi, just before 5pm, was scheduled to attend a dinner with prime minister Sheikh Hasina and president Zillur Rahman later in the evening. He will also meet with Nobel Laureate Muhammad Yunus during his visit. Kalam, who served as India's eleventh president from 2002 to 2007, was a driving force behind India's plans to become a developed and knowledge-based super power by 2020. He was born in Rameshwaram at Tamil Nadu in India, and graduated from Madras Institute of Technology in Aeronautical Engineering. Kalam, also one of the architects of India's nuclear programme, has been invited to deliver a lecture to faculty members and students of the University of Information Technology and Sciences in Dhaka on Monday. "Former Indian president APJ Abdul Kalam has kindly agreed to deliver the convocation speech," Abdul Aziz, vice-chancellor of UITS, told bdnews24.com. President Zillur Rahman will preside over the first annual convocation of the university at the Bangladesh-China Friendship Conference Centre. The Indian high commission has said Kalam will also visit Dhaka University and Viquarunnessa Noon School and College, where he is expected to talk with students and staff. bd
